data.name: La Marea
data.description:
Artist digital painting 
*no ai
PNG 9000px by 7200px
at 300ppi

I chose the title La Marea (Spanish for "the tide") as I wanted a link to Solana's history. 

Solana was named after a small beach town North of San Diego called Solana Beach, where Anatoly, Greg and Stephen lived and surfed for three years when they worked for Qualcomm. Solana is also Spanish for warm wind.

I picked tide because it has a massive impact on surfing and while you're out in the waves you're constantly adapting to the changing conditions. There's also a phrase, "the tides of change" which I think captures nicely where we are in the transition from web2 to web3. The Solana blockchain is perfectly positioned to make the most of this.

data.name: Blue Crush
data.description: Blue Crush, 2021, 4'x6', oil on canvas - Blue Crush is a study in composition and colour using both figurative and abstract minimalist features. The character, looking up to an illuminated doorway into the sky, is the only element residing in both of these graphic worlds divided by the horizon line. The upper part is a void of blue with a simple bright shape at its core. The bottom is a complex shoreline from which light reflects and life emerges. I mixed several blues trying to replicate the colour of the sky along the ocean at its earliest light.
